name: Plank
description: This is a fantastic exercise for your core that can be done in loads of different ways, depending on what you want to achieve. You can also perform a plank at both high and low intensity levels.

name: Squat
description: To achieve the best results, use a heavy weight, with fewer reps to increase strength and muscle mass, or use lighter weights (or simply your body weight) with explosive plyometric movements to develop your power and speed.

name: Box Jump
description: This is a plyometric movement (i.e. a quick, movement that starts with a muscle engthening action, immediately followed by a muscle shortening one) that will help develop strength and power in your legs, specifically the hamstrings, glutes and quads.

name: Bench Press
description: An exercise that’s key for building upper body strength. To perform this exercise properly, you’ll need to use an Olympic bar or dumbbells for better muscle recruitment.

name: Treadmill Interval Sprints
description: Playing a game for 90 minutes requires you to have great endurance combined with the ability to put in short bursts of maximum effort. Try a TABATA-style 20 second sprint combined with 10 second recovery and repeat several times to get the full benefit.

name: Bosu Squats
description: This is a fantastic exercise for your core that can be done in loads of different ways, depending on what you want to achieve. You can also perform a plank at both high and low intensity levels.

name: Bosu Squats
description: Using a foam roller both before and after exercise helps massage away knots and tightness in your muscles, which in turn helps prevent injuries and de-stresses the body so it can work more efficiently. It also increases flexibility, all aiding in the much-needed recovery and maintenance process to ensure peak performance throughout a long season.

name: Yoga
description: Sometimes getting excited students to take a break and enjoy nature can be a daunting task. With Garden Yoga partner students up and let them choose a spot outside and enjoy the calmness for a bit!

name: Chin up
description: Do It: Standing on a box or bench, grab the bar with an underhand grip, then jump up so that your chin touches it (a). Pause, then lower yourself as slowly as possible, aiming for about five to 10 seconds (b). Once your arms are fully extended, let go of the bar and step back onto the box.
